{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/mastering-file-and-text-manipulation-with-awk-utility-65fc09d56bef", "time": 1683015491.894125, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/mastering-file-and-text-manipulation-with-awk-utility-65fc09d56bef/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Mastering File And Text Manipulation With Awk Utility | by Alireza Mika | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Mastering File And Text Manipulation With Awk Utility", "description": "As software developers, system administrators and data scientists, working with files and manipulating them is a frequent and important part of our day to day job. Knowing how to work with text files\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://www.gnu.org/software/gawk/manual/gawk.html#Non_002dUnix-Installation", "anchor_text": "GNU manual", "paragraph_index": 4}, {"url": "https://www.tutorialspoint.com/awk/awk_built_in_variables.htm", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 18}, {"url": "https://www.tutorialspoint.com/awk/awk_built_in_functions.htm", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 24}, {"url": "https://www.gnu.org/software/gawk/manual/gawk.html\\", "anchor_text": "The GNU Awk User\u2019s Guide", "paragraph_index": 25}], "all_paragraphs": ["As software developers, system administrators and data scientists, working with files and manipulating them is a frequent and important part of our day to day job. Knowing how to work with text files and applying desired changes to them in a quick and efficient way can save us a considerable amount of time.", "In this article I\u2019m going to introduce you to Awk command, a very powerful text-processing tool which can do complex text processing tasks with one or a few lines of code. You may tend to use your favorite programming languages like Python, Java, C, \u2026 to do these kind of tasks, but after reading this tutorial you will realize doing many of them with Awk is just simpler and more efficient.", "I\u2019ll try to demonstrate Awk\u2019s usage by providing basic examples of how to solve common text processing tasks with it.", "Awk is available by default on most Unix distributions. In case you don\u2019t have it, you can use the following commands to install it.", "If you are using Microsoft Windows, check the GNU manual for installation instructions.", "Awk workflow is simple. It reads a line from input stream, executes specified commands on it, and repeats this procedure until the end of file.", "There\u2019s also BEGIN and END blocks, which you can use to execute some commands before and after the repeated procedure.", "Awk command\u2019s basic structure is like this:", "Consider a text file input.txt with the following content:", "It will run {print} for each line which is just printing it. So the output will be same as the input.", "Here we want to only print the name (first word) and age (second word) of each person separated by a tab.", "In the above example, $1 and $2 represent the first and the second fields from each input line. $0 represents the whole line.", "Here we define a variable as count, increment it when reading each line and print it at the first of the line.", "Note that we can also remove the -v count=0 part. It will be defined implicitly with the value of 0:", "Awk programming language supports conditions too.", "We can achieve this by using dictionaries and loops.", "Here we have a dictionary named my_dict. For each line, the key is the third word (country name) and we increase its value by 1. After the END keyword we can write the END Block commands which we have explained at the workflow section. Here at the END block we loop on the dictionary and print its (key, value) pairs.", "NR is a built-in variable which represents the current record number. So at the END block, it will be equal to the total number of lines.", "You can see other Awk built-in variables here.", "We can use regular expressions with Awk.", "Here we specify that the first word $1 should match the regular expression [sS].", "You can set the regular expression used to separate fields using -F option.", "Consider having this file as input.csv:", "In this example we will show how to create and use functions. Also we will add our code to a file named prog.awk instead of writing it as an input argument. We also print our output to a file named output.txt.", "Awk has also some built-in functions which you can check here.", "In this article we showed the Awk command\u2019s workflow and by providing some examples we saw that Awk is a powerful and flexible text processing tool which can be used in many scenarios. You can read The GNU Awk User\u2019s Guide for more detailed instructions.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F65fc09d56bef&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fmastering-file-and-text-manipulation-with-awk-utility-65fc09d56bef&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fmastering-file-and-text-manipulation-with-awk-utility-65fc09d56bef&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/search?source=---two_column_layout_nav----